{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8a483145-0994-416e-8b85-97054e06c4ac","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Change base images\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then verify:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version        # should show 11.0.x\ndotnet build\ndotnet test             # if you have tests\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages with `.NET 10`-specific versions (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`) and update them to their 11.x releases.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"157b9eec-c8c4-4669-acd6-d8a46d542092","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":309,"requestId":"6812:13861F:10CC137:1523A90:69FFE344"},"id":"37c588c2-0b11-4d27-98d3-7f94947bc521","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:45:47.435Z","parentId":"430e32a4-2900-431b-ab43-a05981c4c30e"}
